        <Requirement>The organization must ensure that it can meet the requirements for the products and services to be offered to customers. The organization shall perform a review before committing to supply products and services to a customer, and this shall include: a) requirements specified by the customer, including requirements for delivery and post-delivery activities; b) requirements not specified by the customer but necessary with regard to specified or intended use, when known; c) requirements specified by the organization; d) regulatory requirements applicable to the Products and Services; e) requirements in contract or order that differ from previously stated requirements. The organization must ensure that requirements in contracts or orders that differ from previously specified requirements are clarified and addressed. Even if the customer does not make a documented claim, the customer's claim must still be confirmed by the organization before the order is accepted. NOTE In certain situations, e.g. when selling over the Internet, it is impractical to do a formal review for each order. The review may instead refer to relevant product information, e.g. catalogs.Keep documented information The organization must, to the extent applicable, keep documented information about: a) the results of the review; b) any new requirements for the products and services.</Requirement>
