        <Requirement>The organization must produce products and perform services under controlled and controlled forms. This means that, to the extent applicable, the organization must: a) have access to documented information that defines: 1) characteristics of the products and services to be offered or the activities to be performed; 2) the results to be achieved; b) have access to and use appropriate monitoring and measurement resources; c) introduce monitoring and measurement, to verify at appropriate times that criteria for the control and control of processes or their results have been met and that products and services conform to acceptance criteria; d) use the appropriate infrastructure and environment to carry out processes; e) appoint competent staff and specify relevant qualification requirements; f) validate and periodically revalidate the ability of processes to achieve planned results for the production of products and the performance of services, where the result cannot be verified by subsequent monitoring or measurement; g) put in place measures to prevent human error; h) perform release, delivery and post-delivery activities.</Requirement>
