        <Requirement>8.7.1The organization must ensure that deviant process results, i.e. those that do not meet set requirements are identified, controlled and controlled, so that unintended use or delivery is prevented. The organization must take appropriate measures based on the nature of the deviation and its impact on the compliance of the products and services with requirements. This shall also include deviating products and services that are discovered after products have been delivered and during or after the performance of services. The organization must handle deviant process results in one or more of the following ways: a) correct; b) sort, separate, return or cancel a delivery of products and services; c) inform the customer; d) obtain approval for supply under exemption. Compliance with the requirements must be verified when deviant process results are corrected. 8.7.2The organization shall maintain documented information that: a) describes the deviation; b) describes actions taken; c) describes delivery dispensations obtained; d) shows which responsible body decided on action for the deviation.</Requirement>
