    <Section standardNo="9.2">
      <Title>Internal audit</Title>
      <Item number="53.0">
        <Requirement>9.2.1 The organization shall, at planned intervals, carry out internal audits to obtain information on whether the quality management system: a) complies with: 1) the organization's own requirements for its quality management system; 2) the requirements of this standard; b) has been implemented and maintained in an appropriate manner.9.2.2The organization shall: a) plan, establish, implement and maintain audit programs, which include frequency, methods, responsibilities, planning requirements and reporting, which shall take into account the significance of the processes concerned, changes affecting the organization and the results of previous audits; b) define audit criteria and scope for each audit; c) select auditors and conduct audits in a manner that ensures the objectivity and independence of the audit process; d) ensure that audit results are reported to relevant management functions; e) without undue delay take appropriate corrections and corrective measures; f) maintain documented information showing the implementation of the audit program and the audit results. NOTE See SS-EN ISO 19011 for guidance.</Requirement>
