    <Section standardNo="9.3">
      <Title>Management review</Title>
      <Item number="54.0">
        <Requirement>9.3.1 General Top management must have a review of the organization's quality management system at planned intervals to ensure the system's continued suitability, adequacy, effectiveness and compliance with the organization's strategic direction.9.3.2Basis for the management's review The management's review must be planned and carried out taking into account: a) the status of measures decided at the management's previous reviews; b) changes to external and internal matters relevant to the quality management system; c) information on quality performance and impact, which includes trends in: 1) customer satisfaction and feedback from relevant stakeholders; 2) the extent to which the quality objectives have been achieved; 3) process performance and compliance of products and services with requirements; 4) deviations and corrective actions; 5) results from monitoring and measurement; 6) audit results; 7) performance of external suppliers; d) adequacy of resources; e) the effectiveness of risk and opportunity management measures (see section 6.1); f) opportunities for improvement.9.3.3Results of the management's review The management's review must result in i.a. decisions or actions relating to: a) opportunities for improvement; b) need for changes in the quality management system; c) resource requirements. The organization shall maintain documented information showing the results of management reviews</Requirement>
